                     <title xml:lang="en">Latin charter</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Grant by William, son of Ranulf de Flamhang to Roger de Stowe of a piece of land and pasture in Totestoke [co. Suffolk], charged with the yearly payment of 1/2d. to the king for the [Castle] Ward of Norwich. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>See corresponding Hebrew quitclaim: Harley Ch 43 A 64 B.</p>
                     
                     
                     
